  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Repetitive Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation (rTMS) can improve mood and decrease sadness in
      patients with depression.

      In this study, the investigators seek to increase their understanding about how rTMS improves
      depression, and to determine which form of rTMS is most effective for depression, when used
      in combination with antidepressant medication.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will be assigned for 4 treatment arms, receiving either left high frequency plus
      right low frequency, or left high frequency plus right sham, or left sham, plus right low
      frequency, or left sham plus right sham treatment. All subjects will receive treatments for
      10 days and will be followed for another 4 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
